Hello! Over the summer, I led my FRC team through creating our own vision processing software for FRC robots - Astrolabe! We are excited to release it into the community.

Astrolabe is designed to be super easy to use and adapt to. It is designed to run on a coprocessor, where it will host a unique websocket for each connected camera (picamera support coming soon). The entire project is written in python currently, but we will likely write a different back-end eventually. It fully supports apriltag detection and color based object detection, and it does not require a dedicated coprocessor. Interacting with the server is as simple as sending a command over a websocket, so you do not need complicated systems to connect. We designed the client-server interface to be as simple as humanly possible, so programmers will not struggle to adapt to it. This is great software for your team if other systems are to complicated/intimidating. It includes a UI designed for use by even non-programmers for last minute tuning.

Anyways, thanks for reading this, here is the github repository: GitHub - MaxedPC08/Astrolabe: Astrolabe is a vision processing software for FRC teams. It is capable of object detection and apriltag detection, along with calculating a bunch of stuff about the object's location. It is designed to be the easiest vision processing system to use for FRC teams.
Please let me know what you think!
